The paper deals with algorithmic techniques for solving problems on planar graphs and graphs that exclude a fixed apex graph as a minor. This suggests that the paper could belong to categories related to graph theory and algorithms, such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Among these categories, cs.DS and cs.CG seem to be the most likely, as the paper involves dynamic programming techniques and pattern searching in graphs.
